#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.113"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.113:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:0.2"
msgid "11. Yogakkhemivagga "
msgstr "11. Sanctuary "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.113:0.3"
msgid "113. Upassutisutta "
msgstr "113. Listening In "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: nātike → ñātike (si, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.113:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nātike viharati giñjakāvasathe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Nādika in the brick house. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā rahogato paṭisallīno imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then while the Buddha was in private retreat he spoke this exposition of the teaching: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:1.3"
msgid "“cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "“Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.4"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā; "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.5"
msgid "vedanāpaccayā taṇhā; "
msgstr "Feeling is a condition for craving. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.6"
msgid "taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.7"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo; "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.8"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti; "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.9"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition that gives rise to old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.10"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:1.11"
msgid "Jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "Ear … nose … tongue … body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:1.12"
msgid "manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.13"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā; "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.14"
msgid "vedanāpaccayā taṇhā; "
msgstr "Feeling is a condition for craving. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.15"
msgid "taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.16"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo; "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.17"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti; "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.18"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition that gives rise to old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:1.19"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.113:2.1"
msgid "Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.2"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā; "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.3"
msgid "vedanāpaccayā taṇhā. "
msgstr "Feeling is a condition for craving. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.4"
msgid "Tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodhā upādānanirodho; "
msgstr "When that craving fades away and ceases with nothing left over, grasping ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.5"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho; "
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.6"
msgid "bhavanirodhā jātinirodho; "
msgstr "When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.7"
msgid "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.8"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti … pe … "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:2.9"
msgid "jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "Ear … nose … tongue … body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:2.10"
msgid "manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.11"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā; "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.12"
msgid "vedanāpaccayā taṇhā. "
msgstr "Feeling is a condition for craving. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.13"
msgid "Tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodhā upādānanirodho; "
msgstr "When that craving fades away and ceases with nothing left over, grasping ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.14"
msgid "upādānanirodhā … pe … "
msgstr "When grasping ceases … "

msgctxt "sn35.113:2.15"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.91, sc3
#. VAR: upassuti → upassutiṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.113:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bhagavato upassuti ṭhito hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time a certain monk was standing listening in on the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:3.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ upassuti ṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr "The Buddha saw him "

msgctxt "sn35.113:3.3"
msgid "Disvāna taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said, "

msgctxt "sn35.113:3.4"
msgid "“assosi no tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyan”ti? "
msgstr "“Monk, did you hear that exposition of the teaching?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:3.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.113:3.6"
msgid "“Uggaṇhāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ. "
msgstr "“Learn that exposition of the teaching, "

msgctxt "sn35.113:3.7"
msgid "Pariyāpuṇāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ. "
msgstr "memorize it, "

msgctxt "sn35.113:3.8"
msgid "Dhārehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ. "
msgstr "and remember it. "

msgctxt "sn35.113:3.9"
msgid "Atthasañhitoyaṃ, bhikkhu, dhammapariyāyo ādibrahmacariyako”ti. "
msgstr "That exposition of the teaching is beneficial and relates to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.113:3.10"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.113:3.11"
msgid "Yogakkhemivaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.113:4.1"
msgid "Yogakkhemi upādāya, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.113:4.2"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ loko ca seyyo ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.113:4.3"
msgid "Saṃyojanaṃ upādānaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.113:4.4"
msgid "Dve parijānaṃ upassutīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
